                <p>Hi Frans, thanks for using my code ! I don&#8217;t know for sure if this is the reason, but it seems you don&#8217;t create the right HTML tags when the server answer, like :</p>
<p>client.println(&#8220;< !DOCTYPE HTML>&#8220;);<br />
client.println(&#8220;<html>&#8220;);<br />
client.println(&#8220;<meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"5\"/>&#8220;);</p>
<p>and :</p>
<p>client.println(&#8220;<br />&#8220;);<br />
client.println(&#8220;</html>&#8220;);</p>
<p>Try by really taking the original code and just changing the part related to the printing of the analog inputs values (and the WiFi SSID/pass of course)</p>
